rt copy. TINLESS OTHERWISE NOTED ON THE DETATL PAGE ALL LAR RESULTS PERFORMED AT: VARGINS: vasive carcinoma involves the inked right superior margin. Invasive. arcinoma is less than 1 mm from the inked right anterior, inked. right lateral, and inked right posterior margins (see parts 2-5 for. additional margins). VENOUS/LYMPHATIC INVASION: Indeterminate. PERINEURAL INVASION: Present. ADDITIONAL PATHOLOGIC FINDINGS: 1. Metastatic carcinoma in two (2) of five (5) lymph nodes [Two (2). of four (4) positive lymph nodes in level 2 and zero (0) of one (1). in level 3A)) The largest metastatic tumor focus is 4 cm (grossly). Extranodal extension is seen. 2. One (1) lymph node, negative for tumor (anterior soft tissue). 3. Focal carcinoma in situ. 4, Lymphocytic thyroiditis. Parts 4 and 9 of this case were shown in part at the Daily Quality. Assurance Conference. End of Diagnosis. Clinical History: SQUAMOUS CELL CARCINOMA. See. or official report. nal Report signed on. Unofficial lab results - do not file in patient chart. Contact medical records for official chart copy. UNLESS OTHERWISIZ NOTED ONY. RMED AT:",IV,G2,HNSC,35.0,TCGA-BB-4227-01Z-00-DX1.7475866c-90bb-4f62-b44e-adccc731cad8.svs,66.0,BB,4.466666666666667,4.466666666666667,2.833333333333333,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,HNSC,1.0
